The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 09 September is 3,103 (359.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 05 September, there were 110 new confirmed cases (12.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 29 August, there were 53 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 108% (57 extra cases).
